        <abstract> 
<p>Has finished ACR’s article ["The old glaciers of Switzerland and N. Wales" in <hi rend="italic">Peaks, passes, and glaciers</hi>, ed. J. Ball (1859)]. Asks the authority for glacial drifts in Siberia. Wishes ACR would examine the Glen Roy parallel roads and settle the problem.</p> 
            <p>Asks if it is certain that traces of organic remains have been found in Long Mynd beds.</p>
        </abstract>
